Shaafi app
Shaafi is a platform that allows medical professionals to give online consultations and medications. Doctor’s registration status is verified and they are allowed to put their fee details so that patients can get the idea of who is going to provide medication at which cost .

It gives the patients the opportunity to get consultations from expert doctors at their convenient time and place and provides daily health tips to subscribers.

Main Features:
- Doctors and patient registrations
- Time settings for doctors
- Search doctors with specialisations, names and consultation fee ranges
- Appointments
- Video and chat consultations
- Prescriptions and patient medical history reports in PDF format
- Easy payment with ZAAD
- Daily sms and on app health tips
- SMS reminder for new appointment, approval of appointment and coming up appointment.
- Transaction history and payment reports
- Lab Integration
- Patient can search for lab
- Pay for Lab tests
- Upload your lab Reports
- Doctor can prescribe a lab test

Discover the BabyCentre Pregnancy Tracker and Baby App – your perfect companion for pregnancy and parenthood!
Expecting? BabyCentre’s Pregnancy Tracker app is here to guide you every step of the way! Track your pregnancy week by week and day by day with expert pregnancy tips, foetal development videos, and content tailored to your unique pregnancy and parenting journey. Just enter your baby’s due date, and let our pregnancy app bring you personalised guidance, advice, and tools from the start of your pregnancy right through to your baby’s first birthday.
Our BabyCentre Pregnancy and Baby app offers everything you need in one place:
Track your journey with our pregnancy tracker
	•	Get daily updates on how your baby is developing, tailored to your exact stage of pregnancy.
	•	Enjoy a daily news feed with tips on pregnancy nutrition, pregnancy exercise, and pregnancy symptom management.
	•	Weekly pregnancy reminders, pregnancy checklists, and pregnancy insights make staying informed easy and fun!
Instant expert advice for pregnancy at your fingertips
	•	Need answers to your pregnancy questions? Our team of Midwives is here to help with real-time support for any pregnancy questions that come up.
	•	Access hundreds of expert articles on every pregnancy topic from BabyCentre, guiding you from bump to baby.
Join a community of mums and new parents
	•	Connect with mums-to-be in your Birth Club, where you can share, ask, and learn about pregnancy together.
	•	Chat with other parents about baby names, early pregnancy symptoms, baby essentials, and everything else related to pregnancy.
Find the perfect baby name
	•	Looking for a baby name finder? Our Baby Name Tool helps you explore thousands of baby names and meanings for your pregnancy journey.
…and so much more!
	•	Use our due date calculator to track your pregnancy, see interactive foetal development images throughout pregnancy, track your bump in our “Bumpie” pregnancy photo diary, and dive into exclusive “Inside the Uterus” pregnancy videos.
From pregnancy to the first year of your baby’s life, our pregnancy app evolves with you, bringing expert pregnancy advice, a supportive community, and all the essential tools you need for a smooth pregnancy experience.
Download the BabyCentre Pregnancy and Baby App today and enjoy every step of your pregnancy journey!
All health information in our pregnancy app is approved by the BabyCentre Medical Advisory Board and certified by the NHS England Information Standard.

Data loaded in IDV (IMAIOS DICOM Viewer) isn't uploaded on the network to ensure storage safety and security of personal health information of the patients (excluding use of sharing features).
IDV supports DICOM files of all types (ultrasound, scanner, MRI, PET, etc.) and offers several fast and intuitive tools such as scrolling, image manipulation and measurement.
It allows you to easily open any file stored on your device or accessible online for quick viewing whenever you want.
Completely free for personal and non-commercial use, IDV is also accessible in its online version on the website www.imaios.com.

Caution: IDV has not been tested or certified for clinical use. It is NOT approved as a medical device. It cannot be used for primary diagnosis in medical imaging.

The Blood Pressure App is an intuitive and user-friendly blood pressure monitoring app designed to help you take charge of your cardiovascular health. Its easy-to-use interface and powerful features empower you to track, analyze, and manage your blood pressure with ease.

Data Entry After Measurement: 
Record your blood pressure measurements after each reading. You can input systolic, diastolic blood pressure, and pulse. The app also allows you to note pills, arrhythmia, and migraine.

Convenient Statistics: 
The App provides comprehensive and insightful statistics that help you understand your blood pressure trends over time. It generates clear, easy-to-read graphs and charts that display your blood pressure history, allowing you to spot patterns and changes at a glance. You can filter data by date ranges to track progress and share your results with your healthcare provider.

Daily Activity Logging: 
Beyond blood pressure monitoring, the app includes a feature for noting your overall well-being and daily activities. You can track factors like stress levels, physical activity, diet, and more. This information can provide valuable context for your blood pressure readings and help you identify lifestyle factors that may be impacting your health.

User-Friendly Interface: 
The app is designed for simplicity and ease of use, making it suitable for users of all ages.

Our Blood Pressure Monitor is your reliable companion in achieving better blood pressure management and a healthier lifestyle. Take control of your heart health and start your journey toward optimal well-being with this powerful and convenient app.

Good health to you!

The MSF Medical Guidelines app has been developed by Médecins Sans Frontières (MSF) to improve access to medical guidelines for field workers.

The app is easy to find and use, and includes all the latest MSF guidelines and information for medical field workers. Content can be downloaded in high and low quality (for weak data connection) and accessed on mobile at any time. Users will be notified about content updates and the publication of new guidelines.

Among other functions, the app allows you to search through the medical guidelines, organize and save relevant content, and share topics with your contacts.

Comments on how improve the app or suggestions for additional features are welcome.

Blood Sugar & Diabetes Tracker: Your Comprehensive Health Management Solution
Take control of your health with the Blood Sugar & Diabetes Tracker app, designed to make tracking and managing your health simple, efficient, and accessible. Whether you’re monitoring blood sugar levels, medications, A1C, or weight, this app provides the tools you need for better diabetes management and overall health tracking.
Supporting both mg/dL (American system) and mmol/L (British system), our app ensures global compatibility for your blood sugar log conversions.


Core Features
* Blood Sugar Tracking: Record and analyze your daily and monthly blood sugar levels.
* Medication Tracker: Manage and log your medications using a user-friendly medication library.
* A1C Tracker: Monitor your A1C levels for long-term diabetes management.
* Weight Tracker: Keep track of your weight and analyze trends for better health.
* Detailed Reports: Generate easy-to-read reports to share with your doctor or monitor your progress.
* Reminders for Logs: Stay consistent with your health tracking using custom reminders. 
* Notification Popups: Get timely alerts to ensure you never miss important updates or logs.
* Dark Mode Support: Reduce eye strain with our sleek and stylish dark mode.
* View & Generate Reports Instantly: Generate and view detailed health reports with ease.


Why Choose Blood Sugar & Diabetes Tracker?
Our app is designed for anyone looking to stay on top of their health. Whether you’re tracking your progress, managing medications, or aiming to improve your A1C and weight, we’ve got you covered.
Download the Blood Sugar & Diabetes Tracker app today and start your journey toward better health and smarter diabetes management!

It is not a substitute for healthcare professional and does not provide a medical advice. Simple. Free. It can save lives. 

The official IFRC First Aid app gives instant access to the information you need to know to handle the most common first aid emergencies and safety tips for crisis situation. With interactive quizzes and simple step-by-step everyday first aid scenarios, it’s never been easier to learn first aid. 
 
 ■ Engaging and active learning, allowing you to see and track your progress, build your knowledge, and increase confidence in your skills and ability to assist in emergencies.
 ■ Safety tips including water safety and road safety to help you prepare for emergencies.
 ■ Preloaded content means you have access to all information at any time, even without a cellular or WiFi connection.
 ■ Interactive quizzes allow you to earn badges that you can share with your friends and share your lifesaving knowledge.
 ■ Improved multi-lingual capability regardless of the user’s location. 
 ■ Linkages to your local Red Cross or Red Crescent on-site and online training.
 ■ Fully integrated with emergency numbers (such as 911, 999, 112, and others) so you can call for help from the app at any time, even while traveling across borders.

See 4 days (7 on iPad) of your blood glucose tests and meds intake in a single screen, designed specifically to help you see evolutions and compare data from one day to another.
Days are organized in seven predefined periods for easy input and comparisons.

* Enter your blood glucose level, your insulin or meds intake, your carbs eaten for a given period in a single quick input screen

* Easy input of your data by tapping any cell in the logbook

* Multi criteria search system to quickly find the data you need

* Add tags to your records to identify specific food types or circumstance

* (Premium) Backup your data and sync all your devices with iCloud

* Write back your blood glucose and insulin intake into the Apple Health App.

* Automatically import your activity, blood glucose and insulin intake data from the Apple Health App

* Protect access to your data with either FaceID or TouchID 

* Easily see or add a note to any of your input with 3D touch (or long press if your device does not support it)

* Easy to read dashboard of your day and the last 7 & 30 days with the following data:
- Average blood glucose
- Current day activity (either active calories if available or number of steps)
- Number of hypoglycemias
- Number of hyperglycemias
- Your estimated A1c
- Number of insulin units used (fast and slow)
- Quantity of oral meds ingested

* Create reminders for your blood glucose tests

* Create 10 minutes timers for your sugar intakes when experiencing an hypoglycemia

* Hypoglycemia timer: instant one-tap 10 minutes timer to remind you to check your blood glucose after having taken sugar 

* Hypoglycemia alert message : one-tap message sent to pre-chosen contacts with your localization to alert them that you’re having an hypoglycemia

* Multiple graphs to take control of your data:
- Blood glucose over  time
- Average blood glucose per period of the day
- Percent of time spent in each blood glucose state (hypo, normal, hyperglycemia)
- Average blood glucose correlated with your insulin intake over time
- Average blood glucose correlated with your activity over time
- Number of times you’ve hit your blood glucose target per time of the day
All those graphs can be viewed for one day, week, month or year

* Define your blood glucose targets

* Customize your hypo and hyperglycemia limits

* (Premium) Mirror sync: automatically send your data to another person device. Ideal for traveling children.

* (Premium) Export a PDF report of your data to easily communicate with your diabetologist

* (Premium) Dark mode UI

* Export all your data in an easy to use CSV file (usable in any spreadsheet software)

* Siri Shortcuts: use Siri to easily enter data, trigger an hypo timer or send an emergency message

* Receive a weekly summary of your blood sugar levels to see how your improving

صمم تطبيق تشايلدرو خبراء واستشاريي نوم الأطفال للأمهات ليساعد على تنظيم نوم أطفالهن سواء نهارًأ بتنظيم القيلولات أو ليلًا بالتدريج بالإضافة إلى المساعدة على تنظيم وتقليل الرضعات والنوم في سرير منفصل عن الوالدين للوصول إلى نوم عميق وصحي.
 تدريب نوم الأطفال الرضع
تشايلدرو هو أول تطبيق عربي يساعد الأمهات على تنظيم ساعات نوم الأطفال الرضع بشكل علمي وآمن من خلال طرق ناجحة وتدريجية بدون الإعتماد على أساليب سريعة تزيد من بكاء الرضع.
مناسب للأطفال من سن 0 وحتى 3 سنوات
لدينا برامج متنوعة لتنظيم النوم بالتدريج وتقليل الرضعات لتناسب عمر طفلك وشخصيته وظروف بيتك أي أنك ستحصلين على خطة مخصصة تلائمك تمامًا وتلائم طفلك.
 جدول يومي تفاعلي
فقط بإدخال موعد استيقاظ طفلك يوميًا سيساعدك التطبيق على معرفة أفضل الأوقات المناسبة للنوم والأكل واللعب من خلال الجدول الذكي.وبالإضافة لذلك ستجدين قوائم عمل يومية حسب البرنامج الخاص بطفلك. 
 مدربيي واستشاريي نوم معتمدين
لدينا مدربيي ومقدمي رعاية للأطفال معتمدين من استراليا للأطفال حديثي الولادة وحتى سن 5 سنوات لذلك نقدم حلول وبرامج فعالة تناسب طفلك لنصل معًا إلى هدفك بشكل علمي وآمن.
 ليالي هادئة لكِ ولطفلك
زيادة ساعات النوم عند الأطفال والحصول على ليالي هادئة ونوم صحي ليس أمرًا مستحيلًا. فالتطبيق يساعدك على معرفة أفضل طريقة لجعل طفلك ينام بشكل متواصل من 8-10 ساعات يوميًا خلال الليل في وقت قياسي.
 دعم ومساعدة طوال الوقت
يهمنا نجاح برنامج النوم ومساندتك طوال الوقت لذا يمكنك التواصل مع استشاري نوم الأطفال بسهولة وطلب المساعدة في جميع الأوقات من خلال خدمة الرسائل وبضغطة زر واحدة.
في تشايلدرو نهدف بأن ترين مع الوقت من خلال النتائج أنه من الممكن علاج اضطرابات النوم عند الأطفال والوصول إلى النوم العميق عند الأطفال باتباع خطوات بسيطة وأن طفلك واحد من هؤلاء الأطفال ويمكن تدريبه بسهولة

The most popular and innovative app of its kind, SnoreLab records, measures and tracks your snoring and helps you to discover effective ways to reduce it.

SnoreLab has monitored more than 50 million nights of sleep and has helped millions of people to better understand or even eliminate their snoring problem.

The app is very easy to use: simply set SnoreLab running next to your bed whilst you sleep. In the morning you will discover your Snore Score, exactly when and how loudly you snored, and listen to some highlights!

SnoreLab lets you log and track lifestyle factors and any snoring remedies so you can see how they impact your snoring.

SnoreLab is attracting endorsements from doctors, dentists and users alike. The app can be useful in medical consultations when investigating sleep disorders such as sleep apnea.

Are you a room shaker or a snorter? A buzz saw or a whistler? Or do you just purr like a kitten? Discover the truth with SnoreLab! What's your Snore Score?

'An ingenious app' - Mail Online

CGM VISODENT 3D App ist ein Beratungsmodul für Zahnärzte und Patienten. Es enthält grafisches 2D-Bildmaterial von Zähnen und Gebiss-Situationen aus den unterschiedlichen Bereichen der Zahnmedizin incl. zugehöriger textueller Beschreibung. Mit diesen kann in einer Praxis/Klinik die Beratung von Patienten erfolgen. Nicht-Mediziner können sich selbstständig über ihre bevorstehende Behandlung informieren. 
Bei einer Vielzahl des 2D-Bildmaterials ist der Aufruf von 3D-Animationen möglich. Diese Animationen visualisieren den zuvor gewählten 2D-Bildinhalt zusätzlich dreidimensional.
Die App kann auf Smartphones wie auch Tablets eingesetzt werden. Die enthaltenen Themen sind frei wählbar.
Mit der CGM VISODENT 3D App – Version 2.0 wird Anwendern, die das Praxisverwaltungssystem Z1 einsetzen, die Möglichkeit gegeben, aus der App heraus eine Patientensuche zu starten. Nach erfolgreicher Suche wird der aktuelle Patientenbefund geladen und gleichzeitig bei Vorliegen einer Behandlungsbedürftigkeit automatisch eine Regel- und Alternativversorgung in der App dargestellt.
